   </p>
            </li>

        <li>
          <h4>2. Create the UI code </h4>

          <p>
            Clone existing apps or create yours using the <a href="/framework">javascript framework.</a> No need to install something. Code
            online. The code is also saved to GIST to manage the versioning.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li><h4>3. Update the structure of the Answers table </h4>

          <p>VolatileTask generates a basic Google fusion table to store
            the
            answers of the users. This table contains initially 3 required columns: task_id = the id of the task answered, created_at= the
            datetime of
            the answer, user_id= the user's ID.
            Add specific columns according to the structure of your answer data.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li><h4>4. Enjoy !</h4>
          <p>
          Your app is ready. You can embed the app on your web site or display its QRcode so people can complete tasks via their mobile phones. 

