       <h4> How does it work internally</h4>   
          Once the indexation of the GF tasks table done and a GF answers table generated, the framework will organize the tasks using a <i>parallel model</i>.
          <br/>In a parallel model, a set of volunteers performs independently the same task.
          So, according to the redundancy criteria provided during the creation of the app, each task will be assigned to 1 or several users. furthermore in this model a post data processing is generally required to aggregate the answers of different users (e.g. average or consensual) in order to generate a collective output. 

          <br/>A parallel model is generally fine for simple tasks but certainly limited for more complex ones.  <a href="http://nico.maisonneuve.free.fr/blog/index.php/2012/crowdsourcing-satellite-imagery-part-2-iterative-vs-parallel-human-organisations/">Other models of organisation</a> are possible and a "organisation design" tool will be developed if I have time. Below an example of a parallel model to annotate maps collaboratively, fitting with the GIS 

